$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Common\LanguageResources

{ InstallLanguage

  The value of `InstallLanguage` is the → Windows/development/Internationalization/language#windows-languages[language id] (type `REG_DWORD`) of the chosen *default language* 
  (→ Microsoft/Office[Office]: File -> Options -> Language -> *Choose Editing Languages*)
 
}
{ PreferredEditingLanguage and PreviousPreferredEditingLanguage

  Unlike `InstallLanguage`, the data type of these two values is `REG_SZ`.

  The following script changes what in → Microsoft/Office/Excel[Excel] can be changed under File -> Options -> Languages -> Choose Editing Language

  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Common/LanguageResources/preferred-editing-language.ps1||

}

sa:
  Some of the values of this → Windows/registry[registry] key can be configured with → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/SETLANG_EXE[`SETLANG.EXE`].
